==English==
===Etymology===
Modern Latin, from [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[έντασις]]''' (''entasis'') "tension, straining", from '''[[εντείνω]]''' (''enteino'') "to stretch or strain tight".

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'ɛntəsɪs/

===Noun===
'''entasis'''
# a slight [[curvature]] introduced into the shaft of a column to create the impression of [[concavity]]; a deliberate [[bowing]]

[[zh:entasis]]